sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Target Corp (Symbol: TGT), where a total of 52,110 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 5.2 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 84.6% of TGT's average daily trading volume over the past month of 6.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $77.50 strike call option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 6,403 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 640,300 underlying shares of TGT.

Dollar Tree Inc (Symbol: DLTR) saw options trading volume of 21,085 contracts, representing approximately 2.1 million underlying shares or approximately 78.7% of DLTR's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.7 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $110 strike call option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 5,215 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 521,500 underlying shares of DLTR.

Below is a chart showing DLTR's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $110 strike highlighted in orange:

And Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) options are showing a volume of 51,772 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 5.2 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 77.7% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 6.7 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $125 strike call option expiring March 16, 2018 , with 6,954 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 695,400 underlying shares of CRM.
